<subSubSection id="C379979F163D367EAE76FB29DCB33004" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDCC414163D367EAE76FB29DCB33004" blockId="6.[869,1494,1178,1299]" lastBlockId="7.[94,719,634,787]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B9171806163D367FAE76FB29DDE437A4" bold="true" box="[869,993,1178,1203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum with laterobasal lobe flattened, apex curved downwards, with acute lateral spine; dorsal projections very small, sharp, distal margins sinuous, with acute lateral apex acute, pointing posteriorly; scutellar projection lamellar, long, triangular, nearly symmetrical, regularly narrowing apically. 
<taxonomicName id="4C63BF97163C367EAF1CFD29DCCB31A4" authority="Biffi &amp; Geiser, 2020" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Geiser" authorityYear="2020" box="[527,718,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Peltariosilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9171806163C367EAF1CFD29DCCB31A4" box="[527,718,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Peltariosilis major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A224A57D163C367EAD4DFD09DEB031C4" box="[94,181,698,723]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all other species by the very small dorsal projections of pronotum and by laterobasal lobes flattened dorsally with apex acute curved downwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
